# {{ app_title }}

Cloudflare Worker that serves [Better Auth](https://better-auth.com) and a shadcn/ui login SPA, backed by [Cloudflare D1](https://developers.cloudflare.com/d1/). Generated from the [cloudflare-better-auth-d1 copier template](https://copier.readthedocs.io/).

- Hono Worker with Better Auth mounted at `/api/auth/*`, `drizzle-orm/d1` adapter
- Vite React SPA served via the Worker's `assets` binding, gated so `/api/*` runs on the Worker
- Generated drizzle schema + SQL migration for the four better-auth tables

## Quickstart

All project commands are defined as [mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) tasks. If you don't have mise, `curl https://mise.run | sh` or `brew install mise`.

Copier already ran `mise trust`, `mise install`, and the JS installs when it rendered this project, so bun + node are pinned and dependencies are in place. What's left:

```bash
bunx wrangler login           # one-time CF auth (interactive — see below for headless)
mise init                     # seeds .dev.vars, applies local migrations,
                              # provisions remote D1 + BETTER_AUTH_SECRET,
                              # applies remote migrations
mise dev                      # http://localhost:8787
mise deploy                   # ship to *.workers.dev
```

`init` only provisions remote resources when wrangler is already authenticated. If you skipped `wrangler login`, it prints a hint and moves on — run `mise run d1:create && mise run secret:put && mise run migrate:remote` yourself once you've logged in. `d1:create` and `secret:put` require `jq`.

### Headless auth (no browser)

`bunx wrangler login` fails on a headless box with `Missing file or directory: xdg-open`. Instead, export credentials as env vars (either a scoped `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` — preferred, create at <https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens> with Workers Scripts:Edit + D1:Edit + Secrets:Edit — or the `CLOUDFLARE_API_KEY` + `CLOUDFLARE_EMAIL` global-key pair) and pass `--headless` to `init`:

```bash
export CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=...
mise init --headless          # validates via `wrangler whoami`, then provisions D1,
                              # uploads the auth secret, and applies remote migrations
```

With a secret manager like [fnox](https://github.com/jdx/fnox): `fnox exec -- mise init --headless`.

### Push to a new private GitHub repo

Pass `--github` to `init` to `git init` (if needed), stage + commit the template content, create a private GitHub repo named `{{ project_slug }}`, and push `main` with upstream set. Requires the [gh CLI](https://cli.github.com) authenticated (`gh auth login`). Combine with `--headless` if you want both in one shot: `mise init --headless --github`.

## Tasks

Run `mise tasks` for the full list. Highlights:

| Task | What it does |
|---|---|
| `mise run dev` | Build the SPA (if stale) and start `wrangler dev` |
| `mise run web:build` | Build the Vite SPA into `web/dist` (source-tracked — re-runs only when inputs change) |
| `mise run typecheck` | Typecheck Worker + web |
| `mise run auth:generate` | Regenerate `src/db/schema.ts` from `better-auth.config.ts` |
| `mise run db:generate` | `drizzle-kit generate` (emit SQL from the new schema) |
| `mise run migrate:local` / `migrate:remote` | Apply D1 migrations |
| `mise run secret:put` | Ensure `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` is set on the remote Worker (idempotent) |
| `mise run deploy` | Build the SPA and `wrangler deploy` |
| `mise run teardown` | Delete the remote Worker and D1 database (irreversible) |

## Deploy

```bash
mise deploy
```

On the first deploy, `mise deploy` captures the `*.workers.dev` URL that wrangler prints, patches `vars.BETTER_AUTH_URL` in `wrangler.jsonc`, and redeploys once so Better Auth sees a matching origin. For a custom domain, edit `vars.BETTER_AUTH_URL` yourself before the first deploy and the auto-patch stays out of the way.

`mise init` already uploaded `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` and applied remote migrations. Use `mise run secret:put` to rotate the secret (skips when already set — delete it in the dashboard first to force a new one) and `mise run migrate:remote` after adding new migrations.

See `CLAUDE.md` for the full architecture, schema-generation flow, and auth-specific gotchas.
